    "passage_text": "The old house stood at the edge of the cliff, a silent sentinel watching over the turbulent sea. Its windows, like tired eyes, caught the fading light of the autumn sun. Inside, the air was thick with the scent of dried lavender and old paper, a testament to years of quiet solitude. Elara walked through the corridors, her footsteps echoing against the polished mahogany floors. Every creak of the wood seemed to whisper a secret from the past, a memory long buried under the weight of time. She reached for the heavy velvet curtains, pulling them back to reveal the churning grey waters below. The salt spray misted against the glass, blurring the boundary between the safe sanctuary of the house and the untamed power of the ocean outside. In that moment, she felt both anchored and adrift, a part of the history she was trying to escape."
